==English==

===Etymology===
The term dates from the 1960s or earlier, a hybrid of the Greek [[poly]] for [[many]] and the Latin [[amor]] for [[love]].

===Adjective===
'''polyamorous'''

# Following one of various practices of having [[relationship]]s with multiple [[partner]]s, with the knowledge and consent of all involved.
# Having personal beliefs regarding [[relationship]]s that are compatible with [[polyamory]], regardless of one's experience or current practices.

